<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id778e44b2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s428a"><num value="428a">§ 428a.</num><heading> Qualifications of members of commission</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In appointing the members of the commission created by <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s428">section 428 of this title</ref> the Secretary of the Interior shall, as far as practicable, select persons familiar with the terrain of the battlefield of Fort Donelson, Tennessee, and the historical events associated therewith.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id778e44b3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1928-03-26/ch248/s2">Mar. 26, 1928, ch. 248, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/367">45 Stat. 367</ref>; Ex. Ord. No. 6166, § 2, <date date="1933-06-10">June 10, 1933</date>; Ex. Ord. No. 6228, § 1, <date date="1933-07-28">July 28, 1933</date>; <ref href="/us/pl/86/738/s5">Pub. L. 86–738, § 5</ref>, <date date="1960-09-08">Sept. 8, 1960</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/74/876">74 Stat. 876</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
